2050.name: Aquaculture production (metric tons)
2050.description: Aquaculture is understood to mean the farming of aquatic organisms including fish, molluscs, crustaceans and aquatic plants. Aquaculture production specifically refers to output from aquaculture activities, which are designated for final harvest for consumption.
2050.s_name: World Bank – WDI: Aquaculture production (metric tons)

source.name: World Bank – WDI: Aquaculture production (metric tons)
source.additionalInfo: Statistical concept and methodology: Aquaculture production specifically refers to output from aquaculture activities, which are designated for final harvest for consumption. At this time, harvest for ornamental purposes is not included.
